,000 in annual recurring revenue from three signed enterprise contracts, highlighting its significant business impact [24].\n\nWould you like more information about how this might affect the launch timeline or other related risks?","sources_used":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OaWf-KzyUEnNp_aUm9dGc9g9scyr-x0n/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"AI_Search_Architecture.pdf","sourceId":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1cWDQ4mEaj5ym2QFicMP-AEp4v9yg2qMK/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Engineering_AllHands_Oct28_2024.pdf","sourceId":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1pcwDpaqMVClET6mfadGy_oCYn4FgigJ-/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"JIRA_INFRA-1247_AWS_EU_Blocker.pdf","sourceId":"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-z6r1IrvdWltGMYOjsUlg6t7A9WU6xt_/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Product_Roadmap_2025.pdf","sourceId":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1blwqBYR0kIAz8lgFDkzo6uRQBs0Vkkks/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Q4_2024_OKRs.pdf","sourceId":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"48f70248-463f-42cc-9296-330711b86ac3","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1MHcvhX7gaYOpy4WPPfr8CXtrPKr1RxBJ/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Team_Quick_Reference_Guide.pdf","sourceId":"48f70248-463f-42cc-9296-330711b86ac3","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"citationIndexMap":{}}},"createdAt":"2026-02-24T09:08:33.852Z"},{"id":"709b76cd-247d-4e8a-b05b-329ef78d3585","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"user","content":"What are our Q4 OKRs for the AI search project?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":null,"metadataJson":null,"createdAt":"2026-02-24T09:17:55.555Z"},{"id":"43906f6f-d5f6-4dcb-b4c9-bc65998317f0","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"user","content":"What are our Q4 OKRs for the AI search project?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":null,"metadataJson":null,"createdAt":"2026-02-24T09:18:25.632Z"},{"id":"0defe415-66da-4fbe-b5a5-e9892a06419e","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"assistant","content":"The Q4 OKRs for the AI search project focus on launching the semantic search capability by November 15, 2024. This involves replacing the existing keyword-based search with a new, more advanced system that leverages vector embeddings and large language models to improve search accuracy and latency. The objective is to enhance the user experience significantly, allowing for natural language queries with a target latency of under 2 seconds for the 95th percentile of queries [3][5].\n\n- This involves replacing the existing keyword-based search with a new, more advanced system that leverages vector embeddings and large language models to improve search accuracy and latency. [1]\n- The objective is to enhance the user experience significantly, allowing for natural language queries with a target latency of under 2 seconds for the 95th percentile of queries [3][5].\n\nWould you like more details on the specific metrics or the implementation plan for these objectives?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":[],"metadataJson":{"response":{"answer":"The Q4 OKRs for the AI search project focus on launching the semantic search capability by November 15, 2024. This involves replacing the existing keyword-based search with a new, more advanced system that leverages vector embeddings and large language models to improve search accuracy and latency. The objective is to enhance the user experience significantly, allowing for natural language queries with a target latency of under 2 seconds for the 95th percentile of queries [3][5].\n\n- This involves replacing the existing keyword-based search with a new, more advanced system that leverages vector embeddings and large language models to improve search accuracy and latency. [1]\n- The objective is to enhance the user experience significantly, allowing for natural language queries with a target latency of under 2 seconds for the 95th percentile of queries [3][5].\n\nWould you like more details on the specific metrics or the implementation plan for these objectives?","bullets":[],"sources":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OaWf-KzyUEnNp_aUm9dGc9g9scyr-x0n/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"AI_Search_Architecture.pdf","sourceId":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-z6r1IrvdWltGMYOjsUlg6t7A9WU6xt_/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Product_Roadmap_2025.pdf","sourceId":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1cWDQ4mEaj5ym2QFicMP-AEp4v9yg2qMK/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Engineering_AllHands_Oct28_2024.pdf","sourceId":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1blwqBYR0kIAz8lgFDkzo6uRQBs0Vkkks/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Q4_2024_OKRs.pdf","sourceId":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"citations":[],"answer_text":"The Q4 OKRs for the AI search project focus on launching the semantic search capability by November 15, 2024. This involves replacing the existing keyword-based search with a new, more advanced system that leverages vector embeddings and large language models to improve search accuracy and latency. The objective is to enhance the user experience significantly, allowing for natural language queries with a target latency of under 2 seconds for the 95th percentile of queries [3][5].\n\n- This involves replacing the existing keyword-based search with a new, more advanced system that leverages vector embeddings and large language models to improve search accuracy and latency. [1]\n- The objective is to enhance the user experience significantly, allowing for natural language queries with a target latency of under 2 seconds for the 95th percentile of queries [3][5].\n\nWould you like more details on the specific metrics or the implementation plan for these objectives?","sources_used":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OaWf-KzyUEnNp_aUm9dGc9g9scyr-x0n/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"AI_Search_Architecture.pdf","sourceId":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-z6r1IrvdWltGMYOjsUlg6t7A9WU6xt_/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Product_Roadmap_2025.pdf","sourceId":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1cWDQ4mEaj5ym2QFicMP-AEp4v9yg2qMK/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Engineering_AllHands_Oct28_2024.pdf","sourceId":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1blwqBYR0kIAz8lgFDkzo6uRQBs0Vkkks/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Q4_2024_OKRs.pdf","sourceId":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"citationIndexMap":{}}},"createdAt":"2026-02-24T09:18:29.236Z"},{"id":"281110ca-31a4-4b95-9e7e-af39d0673efe","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"assistant","content":"The Q4 OKRs for the AI search project include several key objectives and metrics. One of the main goals is to launch the semantic search feature by November 15, 2024. This involves replacing the existing keyword-based search with a more advanced semantic search powered by vector embeddings and large language models (LLMs).\n\n- A critical milestone is the successful launch of the AI-powered search by mid-November, ensuring it meets latency and accuracy benchmarks during internal and limited beta testing phases [5][9].\n- The project also focuses on achieving a 20% improvement in the \"found answer\" rate compared to the existing search system, which is being tested during the beta phases [5].\n- There are concerns about the budget for vector database costs exceeding the allocated amount, which is a high-risk factor that may affect the financial metrics of this OKR [14].\n- Additionally, there is a lower risk associated with recruitment delays for site reliability engineering positions needed to support the system's infrastructure [9].\n\nWould you like more details on any specific objective or the strategies in place to achieve them?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":[],"metadataJson":{"response":{"answer":"The Q4 OKRs for the AI search project include several key objectives and metrics. One of the main goals is to launch the semantic search feature by November 15, 2024. This involves replacing the existing keyword-based search with a more advanced semantic search powered by vector embeddings and large language models (LLMs).\n\n- A critical milestone is the successful launch of the AI-powered search by mid-November, ensuring it meets latency and accuracy benchmarks during internal and limited beta testing phases [5][9].\n- The project also focuses on achieving a 20% improvement in the \"found answer\" rate compared to the existing search system, which is being tested during the beta phases [5].\n- There are concerns about the budget for vector database costs exceeding the allocated amount, which is a high-risk factor that may affect the financial metrics of this OKR [14].\n- Additionally, there is a lower risk associated with recruitment delays for site reliability engineering positions needed to support the system's infrastructure [9].\n\nWould you like more details on any specific objective or the strategies in place to achieve them?","bullets":[],"sources":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OaWf-KzyUEnNp_aUm9dGc9g9scyr-x0n/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"AI_Search_Architecture.pdf","sourceId":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-z6r1IrvdWltGMYOjsUlg6t7A9WU6xt_/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Product_Roadmap_2025.pdf","sourceId":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1cWDQ4mEaj5ym2QFicMP-AEp4v9yg2qMK/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Engineering_AllHands_Oct28_2024.pdf","sourceId":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1blwqBYR0kIAz8lgFDkzo6uRQBs0Vkkks/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Q4_2024_OKRs.pdf","sourceId":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"citations":[],"answer_text":"The Q4 OKRs for the AI search project include several key objectives and metrics. One of the main goals is to launch the semantic search feature by November 15, 2024. This involves replacing the existing keyword-based search with a more advanced semantic search powered by vector embeddings and large language models (LLMs).\n\n- A critical milestone is the successful launch of the AI-powered search by mid-November, ensuring it meets latency and accuracy benchmarks during internal and limited beta testing phases [5][9].\n- The project also focuses on achieving a 20% improvement in the \"found answer\" rate compared to the existing search system, which is being tested during the beta phases [5].\n- There are concerns about the budget for vector database costs exceeding the allocated amount, which is a high-risk factor that may affect the financial metrics of this OKR [14].\n- Additionally, there is a lower risk associated with recruitment delays for site reliability engineering positions needed to support the system's infrastructure [9].\n\nWould you like more details on any specific objective or the strategies in place to achieve them?","sources_used":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OaWf-KzyUEnNp_aUm9dGc9g9scyr-x0n/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"AI_Search_Architecture.pdf","sourceId":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-z6r1IrvdWltGMYOjsUlg6t7A9WU6xt_/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Product_Roadmap_2025.pdf","sourceId":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1cWDQ4mEaj5ym2QFicMP-AEp4v9yg2qMK/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Engineering_AllHands_Oct28_2024.pdf","sourceId":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1blwqBYR0kIAz8lgFDkzo6uRQBs0Vkkks/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Q4_2024_OKRs.pdf","sourceId":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"citationIndexMap":{}}},"createdAt":"2026-02-24T09:18:31.266Z"},{"id":"5a528de6-04da-45c6-94d9-8b217398c0da","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"user","content":"Are there any blockers for the AI search launch?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":null,"metadataJson":null,"createdAt":"2026-02-24T09:18:42.186Z"},{"id":"e2de3a5e-9f66-4cdf-ad44-1097597c1200","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"assistant","content":"Yes, there is a significant blocker for the AI search launch related to the AWS EU region quota. This issue is critical because it affects the ability to deploy the Pinecone vector database necessary for serving European customers at the required scale. - Jordan Martinez is leading the efforts to resolve this issue, with a deadline set for November 11, 2024.\n\n- Jordan Martinez is leading the efforts to resolve this issue, with a deadline set for November 11, 2024. This is just a few days before the planned launch date of November 15 [12][24].\n- The situation has been escalated to the AWS VP level, with an executive call scheduled for November 1 if the issue is not resolved by then [14][22].\n- The blocker has a substantial business impact, putting at risk $500,000 in annual recurring revenue from three signed enterprise contracts. The inability to serve these customers could also affect GDPR compliance and investor confidence [24].\n- As a mitigation strategy, there is a fallback plan to deploy with 50 instances, which would support 100,000 daily active users instead of the required 200,000, should the full quota not be approved in time [24].\n\nWould you like more information on the potential impacts on the launch timeline or other related risks?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":[],"metadataJson":{"response":{"answer":"Yes, there is a significant blocker for the AI search launch related to the AWS EU region quota. This issue is critical because it affects the ability to deploy the Pinecone vector database necessary for serving European customers at the required scale. - Jordan Martinez is leading the efforts to resolve this issue, with a deadline set for November 11, 2024.\n\n- Jordan Martinez is leading the efforts to resolve this issue, with a deadline set for November 11, 2024. This is just a few days before the planned launch date of November 15 [12][24].\n- The situation has been escalated to the AWS VP level, with an executive call scheduled for November 1 if the issue is not resolved by then [14][22].\n- The blocker has a substantial business impact, putting at risk $500,000 in annual recurring revenue from three signed enterprise contracts. The inability to serve these customers could also affect GDPR compliance and investor confidence [24].\n- As a mitigation strategy, there is a fallback plan to deploy with 50 instances, which would support 100,000 daily active users instead of the required 200,000, should the full quota not be approved in time [24].\n\nWould you like more information on the potential impacts on the launch timeline or other related risks?","bullets":[],"sources":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OaWf-KzyUEnNp_aUm9dGc9g9scyr-x0n/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"AI_Search_Architecture.pdf","sourceId":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1cWDQ4mEaj5ym2QFicMP-AEp4v9yg2qMK/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Engineering_AllHands_Oct28_2024.pdf","sourceId":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1pcwDpaqMVClET6mfadGy_oCYn4FgigJ-/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"JIRA_INFRA-1247_AWS_EU_Blocker.pdf","sourceId":"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-z6r1IrvdWltGMYOjsUlg6t7A9WU6xt_/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Product_Roadmap_2025.pdf","sourceId":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1blwqBYR0kIAz8lgFDkzo6uRQBs0Vkkks/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Q4_2024_OKRs.pdf","sourceId":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"48f70248-463f-42cc-9296-330711b86ac3","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1MHcvhX7gaYOpy4WPPfr8CXtrPKr1RxBJ/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Team_Quick_Reference_Guide.pdf","sourceId":"48f70248-463f-42cc-9296-330711b86ac3","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"citations":[],"answer_text":"Yes, there is a significant blocker for the AI search launch related to the AWS EU region quota. This issue is critical because it affects the ability to deploy the Pinecone vector database necessary for serving European customers at the required scale. - Jordan Martinez is leading the efforts to resolve this issue, with a deadline set for November 11, 2024.\n\n- Jordan Martinez is leading the efforts to resolve this issue, with a deadline set for November 11, 2024. This is just a few days before the planned launch date of November 15 [12][24].\n- The situation has been escalated to the AWS VP level, with an executive call scheduled for November 1 if the issue is not resolved by then [14][22].\n- The blocker has a substantial business impact, putting at risk $500,000 in annual recurring revenue from three signed enterprise contracts. The inability to serve these customers could also affect GDPR compliance and investor confidence [24].\n- As a mitigation strategy, there is a fallback plan to deploy with 50 instances, which would support 100,000 daily active users instead of the required 200,000, should the full quota not be approved in time [24].\n\nWould you like more information on the potential impacts on the launch timeline or other related risks?","sources_used":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.co