-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"keyFacts":[],"answer_text":"This involves replacing the existing keyword-based search with a more advanced semantic search powered by vector embeddings and large language models. The goal is to enable natural language queries with a latency of less than 2 seconds for 95% of queries. - This involves replacing the existing keyword-based search with a more advanced semantic search powered by vector embeddings and large language models. [1]\n- The goal is to enable natural language queries with a latency of less than 2 seconds for 95% of queries. [1]\n\n[1]\n\nWould you like me to go deeper on timeline, owners, or risks?","sources_used":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OaWf-KzyUEnNp_aUm9dGc9g9scyr-x0n/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"AI_Search_Architecture.pdf","sourceId":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"relatedSources":[],"citationIndexMap":{"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e":1},"needsClarification":true,"clarifyingQuestions":["Would you like more details on the specific metrics or any potential risks associated with these OKRs?"]}},"createdAt":"2026-02-24T13:36:38.601Z"},{"id":"ce832ad4-2746-4f7e-8b51-2829e8195f7f","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"user","content":"Are there any blockers for the AI search launch?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":null,"metadataJson":null,"createdAt":"2026-02-24T13:36:50.018Z"},{"id":"847494d9-cdd1-4310-8fb1-7694c9c506d4","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"assistant","content":"Yes, there is a critical blocker affecting the AI search launch related to the AWS EU region quota. The team is currently facing a delay in receiving a quota increase for the eu-west-1 region, which is essential for deploying the AI search feature to European customers. This blocker is managed by Jordan Martinez, and there is a hard deadline of November 11 to resolve the issue, as it impacts the November 15 launch date.\n\n- The AWS EU region quota blocker is the most significant risk to the launch. It prevents deploying the necessary infrastructure to support European customers at scale [12][24].\n- Jordan Martinez is leading the efforts to resolve this issue, with daily check-ins and an executive escalation planned if the quota is not approved by November 1 [12][17].\n- The business impact includes a potential $500K ARR at risk from signed contracts with EU enterprise customers like Siemens, Volkswagen, and BNP Paribas [24].\n- A fallback plan involves deploying with reduced capacity (50 instances instead of 100), which would support only 100K daily active users instead of the targeted 200K [24].\n\nWould you like me to pull up more details on the mitigation strategies or the escalation timeline?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":[],"metadataJson":{"response":{"answer":"Yes, there is a critical blocker affecting the AI search launch related to the AWS EU region quota. The team is currently facing a delay in receiving a quota increase for the eu-west-1 region, which is essential for deploying the AI search feature to European customers. This blocker is managed by Jordan Martinez, and there is a hard deadline of November 11 to resolve the issue, as it impacts the November 15 launch date.\n\n- The AWS EU region quota blocker is the most significant risk to the launch. It prevents deploying the necessary infrastructure to support European customers at scale [12][24].\n- Jordan Martinez is leading the efforts to resolve this issue, with daily check-ins and an executive escalation planned if the quota is not approved by November 1 [12][17].\n- The business impact includes a potential $500K ARR at risk from signed contracts with EU enterprise customers like Siemens, Volkswagen, and BNP Paribas [24].\n- A fallback plan involves deploying with reduced capacity (50 instances instead of 100), which would support only 100K daily active users instead of the targeted 200K [24].\n\nWould you like me to pull up more details on the mitigation strategies or the escalation timeline?","bullets":[],"sources":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OaWf-KzyUEnNp_aUm9dGc9g9scyr-x0n/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"AI_Search_Architecture.pdf","sourceId":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1cWDQ4mEaj5ym2QFicMP-AEp4v9yg2qMK/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Engineering_AllHands_Oct28_2024.pdf","sourceId":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1pcwDpaqMVClET6mfadGy_oCYn4FgigJ-/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"JIRA_INFRA-1247_AWS_EU_Blocker.pdf","sourceId":"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-z6r1IrvdWltGMYOjsUlg6t7A9WU6xt_/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Product_Roadmap_2025.pdf","sourceId":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1blwqBYR0kIAz8lgFDkzo6uRQBs0Vkkks/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Q4_2024_OKRs.pdf","sourceId":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"48f70248-463f-42cc-9296-330711b86ac3","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1MHcvhX7gaYOpy4WPPfr8CXtrPKr1RxBJ/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Team_Quick_Reference_Guide.pdf","sourceId":"48f70248-463f-42cc-9296-330711b86ac3","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"citations":[],"answer_text":"Yes, there is a critical blocker affecting the AI search launch related to the AWS EU region quota. The team is currently facing a delay in receiving a quota increase for the eu-west-1 region, which is essential for deploying the AI search feature to European customers. This blocker is managed by Jordan Martinez, and there is a hard deadline of November 11 to resolve the issue, as it impacts the November 15 launch date.\n\n- The AWS EU region quota blocker is the most significant risk to the launch. It prevents deploying the necessary infrastructure to support European customers at scale [12][24].\n- Jordan Martinez is leading the efforts to resolve this issue, with daily check-ins and an executive escalation planned if the quota is not approved by November 1 [12][17].\n- The business impact includes a potential $500K ARR at risk from signed contracts with EU enterprise customers like Siemens, Volkswagen, and BNP Paribas [24].\n- A fallback plan involves deploying with reduced capacity (50 instances instead of 100), which would support only 100K daily active users instead of the targeted 200K [24].\n\nWould you like me to pull up more details on the mitigation strategies or the escalation timeline?","sources_used":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OaWf-KzyUEnNp_aUm9dGc9g9scyr-x0n/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"AI_Search_Architecture.pdf","sourceId":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1cWDQ4mEaj5ym2QFicMP-AEp4v9yg2qMK/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Engineering_AllHands_Oct28_2024.pdf","sourceId":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1pcwDpaqMVClET6mfadGy_oCYn4FgigJ-/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"JIRA_INFRA-1247_AWS_EU_Blocker.pdf","sourceId":"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","ur